Azure Bank Landing Zone — Hub-Spoke Security Architecture
A production-grade Azure landing zone built entirely in Terraform, implementing a hub-spoke network topology for a fictional banking institution aligned with APRA CPS 234 security requirements.
Architecture:
The hub hosts centralised security and connectivity services including Azure Firewall (Basic SKU) with firewall policy and network rule collections controlling inter-spoke traffic, Azure Bastion for secure VM access without public IPs, a Log Analytics Workspace with 30-day retention as the centralised logging sink, Microsoft Sentinel for SIEM/security analytics, and Azure Monitor alert rules with action groups for automated security notifications.
Two spoke VNets connect to the hub via VNet peering with user-defined routes forcing all spoke egress through the Azure Firewall. Spoke1 hosts an identity workload with a Linux VM and NSG. Spoke2 hosts a workload tier with a Linux VMSS behind an internal load balancer with health probes, autoscale rules triggered on CPU thresholds, and an NSG allowing only Bastion and HTTP inbound.
Key technical features:

Single-file Terraform using AVM modules for VNet and peering
Dynamic for loops and for_each across map and list variables for spoke and subnet creation
VNet flow logs replacing deprecated NSG flow logs forwarded to LAW via Traffic Analytics
Firewall diagnostic settings sending application and network rule logs to LAW
Autoscale profile scaling VMSS between 2 and 5 instances based on CPU metrics
Storage account for blob workload simulation in spoke1

Stack: Terraform 1.9+, AzureRM 4.32, Azure Verified Modules, Ubuntu 20.04 ARM64




Errors Encountered when I tried to run terraform apply : (which were fixed)

metric deprecated → changed to enabled_metric
Storage blob wrong arguments → fixed storage_account_name and storage_container_name
SSH key file not found → switched to password auth
Missing closing brace on spoke1 VM → fixed
Subscription ID not set → added to provider block
address_space needed list(string) not string → fixed in variables
Standard_B1s not available → changed to Standard_B2pls_v2 with ARM64 image
Network Watcher already exists → used data source then switched back to resource
NSG flow logs retired June 2025 → switched to VNet flow logs with target_resource_id
Network Watcher 404 → kept as resource block pointing to NetworkWatcherRG
KQL query msg_s column invalid → fixed query to use OperationName
